            "contents": [
                "How often have you sat down wanting nothing more than to stand right back up and pace the room out of fear, only to find yourself saying \"well, this is dumb\"? Well not tonight, my fellow fear junkie. Here are some of the scariest movies out there."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "The Conjuring (2013)",
            "contents": [
                "Ok, chances are you knew this was gonna be on here, but it's fantastically eerie, creepy, and all-around worth clapping for (watch the movie, or at least the trailer, to get that üòâ üëè). If you've already seen it, watch it again. If you haven't, now is the time to get this classic under your belt.",
                "Directed by [James Wan](https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1490123/?ref_=tt_ov_dr), who also did Saw, Aquaman, and The Conjuring 2, The Conjuring is a supposedly true story of the paranormal escapades of paranormal investigators [Ed and Lorraine Warren](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ed_and_Lorraine_Warren).",
                "If you believe in their stories and credibility, this movie will rightly conjure the shit out of your bowels. We're a classy bunch over here.",
                {
                    "iframe": "https://www.youtube.com/embed/ejMMn0t58Lc"
                },
                "<sub>[Watch The Conjuring on Amazon](https://amzn.to/34vUbTA)</sub>"
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "[Sleep Tight (2012)](https://amzn.to/3jGE3mD)",
            "contents": [
                "Sleep is an Italian thriller directed by [Jaume Balaguer√≥](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jaume_Balaguer%C3%B3) where the antagonist is a bellhop who feels nothing and is subtly (and then not-so-subtly) terrorizes his trusting tenants in hopes that they feel similarly down. I mean, the dude even kills himself in his dreams. Nothing.",
                "It is, admittedly, more creepy and disturbing than scary, but because it's so well shot and acted, it deserves a spot on this list.",
                {
                    "iframe": "https://www.youtube.com/embed/hYAPKHQtdmU"
                },
                "<sub>[Watch Sleep Tight on IMDbTV](https://amzn.to/3jGE3mD)</sub>"
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "The Orphanage (2007)",
            "contents": [
                "The Orphanage, directed by [J.A. Bayona](https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1291105/?ref_=tt_ov_dr), is a Spanish film about grief and heartache disguised (incredibly well) as a horror movie. Whereas The Conjuring uses the same tactic of building suspense and fear through a game of hide and clap, The Orphanage does the same (and did it first) of playing a game of hide and knock, but uses it to a much greater effect.",
                {
                    "iframe": "https://www.youtube.com/embed/UkuKtS-N1rM"
                },
                "<sub>[Watch The Orphanage on Amazon](https://amzn.to/2TumEmj)</sub>"
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Scream (1996)",
            "contents": [
                "Scary Movie parodied this movie so much (and so well) that it's easy to forget that Scream is actually scary and *actually good*.",
                "Yes, it's a bit old now and we stand by our declaration that David Arquette is never, ever a good choice, but, thanks to the deft hands of [Wes Craven](https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000127/?ref_=tt_ov_dr), its perfect use of gore, thrills, and self-referential humor keep it current.",
                {
                    "iframe": "https://www.youtube.com/embed/tV4PTwciTuQ"
                },
                "<sub>[Watch Scream on Amazon](https://amzn.to/31JVg8o)</sub>"
            ]
        }
